Utilization:
  - Using it as a DNS sinkhole as well as safe browsing capabilities

  - Possibly will use as a DHCP server as well down the road.

Installation: Headless R-PI

  - I installed Raspberry Pi OS (previously Raspian) first in and I made my R-PI a headless configuration.

  - Ensure SSH is enabled in the configuration files prior to boot

  - Once booted, I nmapped my network (nmap -p22 192.168.xx.xx) to see which IP address was assigned from my DHCP server.

Installation: Pi-Hole

  - Once I found the IP address, I was able to SSH into the R-PI and download Pi-hole utilizing their documentation for install found here: https://docs.pi-hole.net/main/basic-install/

